          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Rural Jobs Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow additional new markets tax credits for investments in the Rural Jobs Zone. The &quot;Rural Jobs Zone&quot; is the area comprised of low-income communities that do not include: (1) a city or town with a population that exceeds 50,000, or (2) any urbanized area contiguous and adjacent to such a city or town. At least 25% of the investments made pursuant to the tax credits allocated by this bill must be in persistent poverty counties, high migration rural counties, or both. </p>]]></text>
